How to run APLUS application using the script files
Note that you need java 1.8.0 version in order to run this application.

For MAC/Linux users:

-> To run usual APLUS with existing modes:

1. cd AlgebraTuTalk
2. ./runAplus.sh

Follow the terminal outcome to open up APLUS with your desired mode

-> To run APLUS in CTI mode:

1. cd AlgebraTuTalk
2. ./runAplus_cti_lightside.sh

"runAplus_cti_lightside.sh" script performs two functions:
	(a) Runs the lightside server ("runAplus_lightside.sh")
	(b) Runs "runAplus.sh" script in CTI mode

For Windows users:

Please choose the appropriate .bat file and run it using the terminal.

For example:

-> to run APLUS in CTI mode, run "runAPLUS-MTMC_CTI_Lightside.bat" file in the terminal.

-> to run APLUS in MTMC mode, run "runAPLUS-MTMC.bat" file in the terminal.
